From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v28 - dce_v8_0 fallback adjusted_clock to mode->clock

After v27 (mode_fixup no-op), CRTC mode_set still fails:
  [drm] *ERROR* [CRTC:41:crtc-0] failed to set mode

Source of error in dce_v8_0_crtc_mode_set:
  if (!amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock)
      return -EINVAL;

amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock comes from amdgpu_atombios_crtc_adjust_pll
which calls ATOM BIOS AdjustDisplayPll command. On PS4 we have known
ATOM BIOS issues (ACPI Error: AE_BAD_PARAMETER during ATOM init), and
that command returns 0 in args.v3.sOutput.ulDispPllFreq.  Result:
adjusted_clock = 0 * 10 = 0 -> -EINVAL -> blank screen.

Workaround: fall back to adjusted_mode->clock (the pixel clock from
the requested mode, which IS valid on PS4 since EDID firmware
provides it).  PLL programming downstream of this point uses
adjusted_clock; if ATOM gave us nothing useful, the mode's own
pixel clock is the natural fallback.

If v28 works:
- "ATOM returned 0, using adjusted_mode->clock=148500 kHz" logs
- No more "failed to set mode"
- CRTC programs successfully
- HDMI shows content (backlight already on per v26)

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
@@ -2553,8 +2553,20 @@
 {
 	struct amdgpu_crtc *amdgpu_crtc = to_amdgpu_crtc(crtc);
 
-	if (!amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock)
-		return -EINVAL;
+	if (!amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock) {
+		/* v28: PS4 ATOM BIOS sometimes returns 0 from
+		 * AdjustDisplayPll (we see "ACPI Error: AE_BAD_PARAMETER"
+		 * during ATOM init).  Without this fallback, mode_set returns
+		 * -EINVAL and CRTC modeset fails -> blank monitor backlight.
+		 * Fall back to the adjusted_mode's pixel clock directly. */
+		if (!adjusted_mode->clock) {
+			pr_warn("dce_v8_0_crtc_mode_set: adjusted_clock=0 AND adjusted_mode->clock=0, can't recover\n");
+			return -EINVAL;
+		}
+		pr_info("dce_v8_0_crtc_mode_set: ATOM returned 0, using adjusted_mode->clock=%d kHz\n",
+			adjusted_mode->clock);
+		amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock = adjusted_mode->clock;
+	}
 
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll(crtc, adjusted_mode);
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_dtd_timing(crtc, adjusted_mode);
